Package fileSystems

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Directory
    The Directory instance has the ability to store other directories and files, manage the stored objects, and provide the way to search, contain and get the stored members.
    File
    The File instance has the ability to store data, edited/overwrite/append to the data store in the instance.
    FileSystem
    The FileSystem instance is responsible for managing the relationship between the directories and files.
    FileSystemLoader
    The FileSystemLoader is a static class that loads data into a file system.
    Lib
    Lib is the class to store constants.
    Path
    Path is the class that acts as the route of a file system.
    PathStack
    The PathStack it a stack of Path that follows LIFO
    SavedDirectory
    SavedDirectory is a save format for the SavedFileSystem.
    SavedFile
    SavedFile is a save format for the SavedFileSystem.
    SavedFileSystem
    SavedFileSystem is responsible of taking a file system and save its status into a local file.
    SystemNavigator
    SystemNavigator is reponsible for tree navigation and directory relations.
